    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I am running Geth on Command line and Geth stops working after server restarts or the Command line closes down. I am using windows so cant use Tmux or anything.\r\n> \r\n> and can I connect the geth with IIS or something ? or I have to forward the port so I can access the RPC from metamask from outsode\r\n\r\nWindows does not support this natively. I am aware of a freeware software (but haven't tested - use at your own risk), https://www.nirsoft.net/utils/nircmd.html\r\n\r\nYou can try and run geth via a .bat script?\r\n\r\n1. Create a file named geth.bat \r\n2. The file should contain the full path to geth and any passed arguments (example: `C:/go-etherum/build/bin/geth --syncmode=.....` \r\n3. `CTRL + R` or Run...\r\n4. `nircmd exec hide \"c:\\path\\to\\geth.bat\"`\r\n\r\nLet us know how you get on.\r\n",
